In EPP caused by <em>FECH</em> mutations, carriers (heterozygotes) and individuals who inherit two low-expression mutations typically do not exhibit symptoms.[9157][9151]<br />
<br />
Female carriers (heterozygotes) for XLP may develop clinical findings related to the disorder. Symptoms may range from those typically observed in affected males, to being completely symptom-free.[10999]&nbsp;
